OL,7,FUnder David Cameron, the Tories
OL,8,Fintroduced a target of spending 0.7%
OL,9,Fof national income on overseas aid,
OL,10,Fwhich was reduced to 0.5% after the
OL,11,Fpandemic and then cut again by the
OL,12,Fcurrent Labour Government to 0.3% to
OL,13,Fpay for greater defence spending.
OL,15,FProposals for a further cut have been
OL,16,Fcriticised by Bond, a group of UK
OL,17,Fdevelopment organisations, whose chief
OL,18,Fexecutive Romilly Greenhill said they
OL,19,Fwere "reckless, short-sighted and
OL,20,Fmorally indefensible".
